Name: Talking Tech: Book Club - Jurassic Park by Michael Crichton
Event Description: Join Rena Youngblood, Executive Director of CMoA; Kaleigh Kendrick, college professor and content developer at Microsoft; and Dedren Snead, futurist and CEO of SUBSUME Media to discuss Jurassic Park by Michael Crichton on Saturday, May 18th at 2 PM.

Name: Talking Tech at CMoA - Rick Spears - Bringing Up ‘Saur’ Subjects: Pixels and Paleontology
Event Description: In the early 1800s, while William Buckland described the first dinosaur specimen, Charles Babbage was dreaming up the first computer. It would be nearly 170 years until dinosaurs and computers merged in the making of 'Jurassic Park.' Since then, digital technology has made great strides in the areas of fossil analysis, specimen replication, and paleo imagery.

Name: Tech Tales - Storytime for Young Explorers - 6/1/24 - Boxitects
Event Description: Boxitects by Kim Smith is the story of two gifted young engineers learning to cooperate and design together. Join us as we kick off our Tech Tales summer series on Saturday, June 1st!

Name: Punch Card Machine Demo
Event Description: The punchcard exhibit starts with a Jacquard Loom, one of the earliest uses of punched cards, which helped to make woven fabric more affordable. Herman Hollerith's invention of electromechanical processing of cards tabulated data for the 1890 census. The IBM family of punch card machines was used for data processing and record-keeping across many industries and academia. Punched cards were even used for matchmaking at the University of Iowa in 1963!

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Amateur (Ham Radio) Radio Camp
Event Description: In this fun, full-day, week long camp, you will learn about the science behind radio transmissions, the Electromagnetic Spectrum, and waves.  Learn how to use this technology to talk to people all over the world and even out of this world on the International Space Station!

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Minecraft Chemistry Labs
Event Description: Students can learn to create and automate their own Minecraft world using Redstone, build structures, and make different compounds.  They can even make pigs fly with helium, or set off underwater TNT!  With this educational program, students will learn the fundamentals of engineering and chemistry, all while having fun in a Minecraft world.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Fractions with Origami
Event Description: Get Creative!  Learn the intriguing Japanese art of origami and produce amazing paper sculptures!  Sharpen your fine motor skills with origami challenges while learning about Numbers and Fractions.  Learn to make dragons, frogs, birds, or flowers and even Ninja star sculptures!

Name: Tech Tales - Storytime for Young Explorers - 6/8/24 - Hedy Lamarr’s Double Life
Event Description: Join us as we celebrate the 83rd anniversary of Hedy Lamarr and George Antheil's filing of their Secret Communications Patent, which laid the foundation for modern Wi-Fi and Bluetooth systems. In honor of this occasion, we will be reading Hedy Lamarr's Double Life: Hollywood Legend and Brilliant Inventor by Laurie Wallmark. This recounts Hedy Lamarr's double life as both a renowned Hollywood actress and an ingenious inventor. Discover how her passion for science and engineering led her to make groundbreaking contributions to the technology we use every day.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: 3D Engineering Design
Event Description: Opportunities in Animation Studios like Disney, Pixar, Electronic Arts Game Designing etc.  Students work in Blender making unique 2D models, learn special effects and 3D animation in this fun camp.  Blender is an open source software which has been used to make some fun and published animations.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Robotics - Code, Build, Challenge!
Event Description: Campers work on Mindstorm EV3 robots and learn to build and code the robot.  Campers will be able to build and program robots to engage in various challenges such as robot obstacle courses, mazes, and more fun and exciting matches.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Animation Nation
Event Description: In this class students discover cartooning & animation basics taking their imagination to a whole new level.  Create fun cartoons, animations and stories and learn to publish them as well!  Learn what goes on in the world of Disney and Cartoon Network.  It is fun filled class and interactive class introducing concepts on Animation.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Python Game Design
Event Description: Python is a widely used, powerful programming language that is used by professionals and hobbyists alike.  With Python you can create a multiplayer live coding strategy game where you can defeat trolls, ogres and other enemies. With Python, you can create games that are both enjoyable and educational, making it a great choice!

Name: Museum After-Hours: Sci-Fi Summer Night
Event Description: Embark on an out-of-this-world evening at the first Museum After-Hours event of the year on Friday, June 14th, from 5:30 to 9:00 PM at Computer Museum of America (CMoA). Celebrate the fun and imagination of all things science fiction by dressing as your favorite Sci-Fi character and exploring artifacts that once seemed like fiction through a scavenger hunt.

Name: Tech Tales - Storytime for Young Explorers - 6/15/24 - T-Bone the Drone
Event Description: This week's exciting read is T-Bone the Drone by Shanda McCloskey. Come and join us for story time as we read about the adventures of a young boy named Lucas and his drone, T-Bone.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: JavaScript Game Design
Event Description: JavaScript is the programming language of the web. It controls everything that happens on a website, like pop-ups, animations, warnings, and autocomplete search boxes.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Sumo Robot Battles
Event Description: Sumo Battles - Robot Battle Arena is the perfect way to get your students excited about robotics and engineering!  With no prior experience needed, students of all levels can join in on the fun and excitement of robot combat.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Junior Adventures with AI
Event Description: Artificial Intelligence (A.I.) is the ability for computers to do things that are considered characteristic of intelligence: language processing, pictorial interpretations, pattern detection and more!  Recently, with the advancement of computing power and ability to process high volumes of data, computers have been able to generate more accurate models that predict responses.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Robots & Sensors - Code, Build, Compete!
Event Description: Students will be able to build and program robots to engage in various projects to learn about motors, sensors, and programming with the Mission to Space robotics challenge.  Students will learn principals of building and programming to be successful in their missions.

Name: Tech Tales - Storytime for Young Explorers - 6/22/24 - There is No Place Like Space
Event Description: In this Dr. Suess inspired book, the Cat in the Hat leads the reader on an adventure to understand the solar system we call home.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Encryption and Cybersecurity
Event Description: Learn about cryptography, digital forensics, IoT (Internet of things), ciphers, and algorithms.  Learn to encrypt and decrypt messages.  Work with teams to detect and stop targeted cyber attacks. Students will work with ' Black hat' & 'White hat' concepts and switch roles to understand both perspectives to develop essential critical thinking and problem solving skills required for a career in cybersecurity.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Minecraft Architecture / Civil Engineering
Event Description: Students learn principles of physics and forces of nature and their effect on structures.  Learn to construct houses, bridges, ships, floating islands, and rollercoasters of the highest quality.  Students start by creating the blueprints of the environment.  As the course progresses, they use the blueprints and apply civil engineering to build the structures and landscape in Minecraft which involves making objects such as working elevators, rail tracks, and more!

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Graphic Design with Adobe Photoshop
Event Description: There is a huge demand for Graphic Designers in Georgia. According to the United States department of Labor the average hourly rate for 90% of Graphic Designers is over $55/hr, and Graphic Designers in Federal Executive branch earn an average of $85,000+ per year.  Future careers are possible a wide range of fields - in addition to advertising and social media, graphic design is needed by companies like NASA and Kellogg's.  Anywhere you see artistic text and images - it was probably created by a graphic artist.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: LEGO Fortnite
Event Description: LEGO Fortnite is a creative fusion of two popular worlds - LEGO and the iconic Fortnite game. In this imaginative crossover, the dynamic and customizable nature of LEGO bricks meets the vibrant and action-packed universe of Fortnite. Builders can recreate iconic Fortnite scenes or invent their brick-based battles, bringing the virtual gaming experience into the tangible realm of LEGO. With mini-figures representing Fortnite characters, players have the opportunity to construct their own miniature Fortnite adventures, combining the thrill of gameplay with the hands-on joy of LEGO building. It's a delightful blend of digital gaming and real-world creativity, offering fans a new way to engage with their favorite Fortnite moments.

Name: Tech Tales - Storytime for Young Explorers - 6/29/24 - What Do You Do With A Problem
Event Description: This week's book is What Do You Do With a Problem? by Kobi Yamada. This story is a heartwarming tale for anyone who has ever dealt with a problem. No one is too young to learn the importance of courage and persistence.

Name: Tech Tales - Storytime for Young Explorers - 7/6/24 - Randy Riley’s Really Big Hit
Event Description: When an asteroid threatens his town, Randy Riley takes the mound and uses his intelligence and problem solving skills to save the day. Come and join us this Saturday!

Name: Punch Card Machine Demo
Event Description: The punchcard exhibit starts with a Jacquard Loom, one of the earliest uses of punched cards, which helped to make woven fabric more affordable. Herman Hollerith's invention of electromechanical processing of cards tabulated data for the 1890 census. The IBM family of punch card machines was used for data processing and record-keeping across many industries and academia. Punched cards were even used for matchmaking at the University of Iowa in 1963!

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Make and Take Home your own GAMING PC
Event Description: In this super fun camp, students learn to design, unassemble, and re-assemble a fully working computer with all the necessary electronic components including a monitor, CPU, keyboard, mouse, and cables.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Robot NASCAR Races
Event Description: This Robotics class targets the absolute beginners. No prior robotics or programming knowledge is required.  Students will be able to build and program robots to engage in various challenges such as battle bots, mazes, and more fun and exciting matches.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Visual 3D Coding with Kodu
Event Description: Learn the basic concepts of programming logic; story, character, and game design. Create a water world, program flying fish, create lava obstacles, score points, manage health and so much more! Your kids will be hooked!

Name: Tech Tales - Storytime for Young Explorers - 7/13/24 - Rosie Revere, Engineer
Event Description: Join us for this week's Tech Tales book reading featuring the inspiring story of Rosie Revere, Engineer by Andrea Beaty. In this heartwarming tale, young inventor Rosie encounters failures and judgment from others but learns to embrace her mistakes and never give up on her passion for engineering. Through her perseverance and determination, Rosie teaches young readers the importance of resilience and creativity in pursuing their dreams.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Build & Code Self Driving Vehicles
Event Description: Keeping pace with a technology driven world, we've developed a hands-on blended learning experience that's fun, rewarding, and challenging.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Game Design with Scratch 3.0
Event Description: Code Smart with MIT Scratch 3.0 is the perfect way to learn the basics of programming!  You'll have a great time learning how to create and play your own video games!

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Mobile & Web App Design
Event Description: Combine scientific knowledge and creativity to take a step into your future by learning a new skillset.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Roblox Business Tycoon
Event Description: Enable and access datastores, so any place in an experience, including places on different servers, you can access and change the same data.  Students will make use of the many tools on Roblox to code amazing games, broadcasting their imaginative capabilities to the world.

Name: Tech Tales - Storytime for Young Explorers - 7/20/24 - A Computer Called Katherine
Event Description: Are you ready to blast off into space and explore the amazing story of Katherine Johnson, one of the main characters in the iconic movie Hidden Figures? In this week's exciting read, A Computer Called Katherine: How Katherine Johnson Helped Put America on the Moon, Tech Tales will be exploring the fantastic story of Katherine Johnson defying race and gender norms to become a critical component of the team that put America into space, and on the moon. In addition, Tech Tales will be having a blast with an out-of-this-world arts and crafts rocket project. Don't miss out on this incredible journey to inspire the young minds in your life.

Name: Talking Tech - Tom Dworschak - Apollo to Artemis: To the Moon and Back - Again
Event Description: To help CMoA celebrate its 5th anniversary and the reason behind our opening date, we welcome back Tom Dworschak, NASA Solar System Ambassador.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: 3D Coding - Design & Code 3D Characters!
Event Description: In this class students discover 3D modeling with simple to use instructions and tools.  Campers will discover 3D modeling with simple to use instructions and tools.  Students can let their imaginations soar by learning to code while producing their own 3D models. They create variables, repeat groups of commands, and create items.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Robot Battles
Event Description: Your camper's robot, which they build and program themselves, will engage in various battle challenges and exciting matches.  Students create Bigger, Stronger, Faster robots designed to fight in the combat arena.  Through these hands on activities, campers learn the principles of building and programming to be successful in their missions.

Name: 2024 Summer Camps: Mad Sciences and Circuits
Event Description: Ideal camp for science lovers.  This exploratory camp is in high demand, exposing students to new experiments and new concepts every day of the week.

Name: Tech Tales - Storytime for Young Explorers - 7/27/24 - Pete the Cat: Out of this World
Event Description: Wrapping up our 2024 Tech Tales series is Pete The Cat: Out of this World by James Dean. Join us as we find out about the amazing adventure Pete has ranging from Space Camp all the way to the Moon and Back!

Name: Punch Card Machine Demo
Event Description:
Ever wonder about the history of the punchcard?

The punchcard exhibit starts with a Jacquard Loom, one of the earliest uses of punched cards, which helped to make woven fabric more affordable. Herman Hollerith's invention of electromechanical processing of cards tabulated data for the 1890 census. The IBM family of punch card machines was used for data processing and record-keeping across many industries and academia. Punched cards were even used for matchmaking at the University of Iowa in 1963!

Come learn more about this history and punch your own souvenir card on an original IBM 029 to take home during the demo.

Saturday, 2 - 4 PM, free with museum membership or admission.
